FBIS4-34665 "drlat121_a_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 Cuba Havana City Water Authority Explains Shortage Havana City Water Authority Explains Shortage FL2206133894 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 22 Jun 94 FL2206133894 Havana Radio Progreso Network Spanish BFN [From the "First Thing" program] [Text] The Havana City water shortage is primarily due to a decrease in the level of the phreatic layer of the Vento Basin and multiple pump breakdowns. Water service authorities have reported that the Havana City municipalities most affected by these shortages include: Centro Habana, Habana Vieja, Cerro, and Plaza de la Revolucion.
